  "@graph": [
    {
      "@id": "gist:exponentOfMeter",
      "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
      "rdfs:comment": [
        "EXAMPLE: In the equation '1 microgram per milliliter = 0.001 x kilogram per meterCubed'\r\n\r\n\t\tthe conversion factor for microgram per milliliter is 0.001\r\n\t\tthe exponent of kilogram is 1\r\n\t\tthe exponent of meter is -3\r\n\t\tall other exponents are zero\r\n\r\n\t\tEvery member of a unit group containing microgram per milliliter must be a multiple of kilogram per meterCubed.",
        "DEFINITION: The exponent of meter in a product of powers of base units."
      ],
      "rdfs:domain": {
